{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fb64d501-9f1d-4b2d-9816-d361a8fb8d53","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nAfter updating, run `dotnet restore` and `dotnet build` to verify everything compiles. Check for any NuGet packages (e.g. `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) that need a major version bump to match .NET 11.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a5cf1e86-67b4-4e72-9f23-ae6c3bf04351","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a general knowledge question - I don't need to look at any files since they described their setup. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":278,"requestId":"A45F:F3EF4:238CEA4:27479DF:6A03D958"},"id":"954097b3-febf-41f0-8a26-bc0afd8b3465","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:52:31.072Z","parentId":"873ba8b5-076a-40e1-aa59-2f5db3faf78c"}
